WEBVTT

00:00:51.933 --> 00:00:55.937
Once in a while when I wake up

00:00:56.896 --> 00:00:59.774
I find myself crying.

00:01:00.483 --> 00:01:02.484
The dream I must have had

00:01:02.485 --> 00:01:04.153
I can never recall.

00:01:04.737 --> 00:01:05.822
But...

00:01:06.364 --> 00:01:07.531
But...

00:01:07.532 --> 00:01:10.784
the sensation that I've lost something

00:01:10.785 --> 00:01:13.913
lingers for a long time after I wake up.

00:01:22.130 --> 00:01:23.631
I'm always searching

00:01:24.382 --> 00:01:26.718
for something, for someone.

00:01:27.302 --> 00:01:30.137
This feeling has possessed me

00:01:30.138 --> 00:01:31.973
I think from that day...

00:01:33.308 --> 00:01:36.394
That day when the stars came falling.

00:01:37.020 --> 00:01:38.603
It was almost as if...

00:01:38.604 --> 00:01:41.357
as if a scene from a dream.

00:01:41.858 --> 00:01:43.401
Nothing more, nothing less

00:01:44.861 --> 00:01:46.904
than a beautiful view.

00:01:47.488 --> 00:01:51.743
Ah, if only our voices speak at night

00:01:53.161 --> 00:01:58.582
could ever reach the very edge
of this world, and the time

00:01:58.583 --> 00:02:03.004
Instead of fading into air and dust

00:02:03.379 --> 00:02:06.465
Then what will the words could ever be?

00:02:06.466 --> 00:02:09.259
Farthest words from 'probably'

00:02:09.260 --> 00:02:16.142
Let's make a promise, that will never fade.
Let's say it together in count of three, oh

00:02:20.229 --> 00:02:29.654
Ah, I'm told that some part of
every wish will be heard

00:02:29.655 --> 00:02:32.324
But lately I lost sight
of the truth in those words

00:02:32.325 --> 00:02:37.120
I can't even remember when I gave up
believing. What could have been the reason?

00:02:37.121 --> 00:02:40.457
Ah, the very moment that the rain will stop

00:02:40.458 --> 00:02:43.126
And the place rainbow born and dies

00:02:43.127 --> 00:02:45.045
And where the end of this life lies

00:02:45.046 --> 00:02:48.633
I've always been insisting there was
something that I've longing for

00:02:53.304 --> 00:02:54.638
One day we'll reach to

00:02:54.639 --> 00:02:58.392
emotions unexplored unprecedented

00:02:58.393 --> 00:03:01.353
We'll high-five love we've yet to discover

00:03:01.354 --> 00:03:03.480
and give a kiss to time

00:03:03.481 --> 00:03:08.903
The five dimensions keep on teasing me.
But I will keep on looking at you, dear

00:03:09.112 --> 00:03:12.532
Let's make a sign for
when we say nice to meet you again

00:03:14.909 --> 00:03:17.995
I'm on my way to you,
chasing after your name

00:03:44.439 --> 00:03:48.317
Taki. Taki.

00:03:49.318 --> 00:03:51.279
Don't you remember me?

00:03:53.531 --> 00:03:54.991
My name is...

00:03:56.742 --> 00:03:57.952
Mitsuha!

00:04:33.946 --> 00:04:36.032
Mitsuha, what are you doing?

00:04:36.199 --> 00:04:39.619
Well, it feels incredibly realistic...

00:04:40.703 --> 00:04:42.746
What? "Mitsuha"?

00:04:42.747 --> 00:04:45.791
Are you half asleep? Breakfast!

00:04:46.083 --> 00:04:46.876
Hurry up!

00:05:07.104 --> 00:05:11.234
What? What?

00:05:18.616 --> 00:05:21.117
Do you want last night's leftovers?

00:05:21.118 --> 00:05:22.994
You can have it.

00:05:22.995 --> 00:05:24.829
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

00:05:24.830 --> 00:05:26.623
Mitsuha, you're late!

00:05:26.624 --> 00:05:28.709
I'll make breakfast tomorrow.

00:05:34.549 --> 00:05:35.966
Is this too much?

00:05:35.967 --> 00:05:37.051
Well. It's okay

00:05:37.635 --> 00:05:39.220
You're normal today.

00:05:39.804 --> 00:05:41.805
You were nuts yesterday.

00:05:41.806 --> 00:05:43.766
What are you talking about?

00:05:45.768 --> 00:05:49.397
Good morning, everyone.

00:05:49.855 --> 00:05:54.151
This is an announcement
from Itomori Town Hall.

00:05:54.694 --> 00:05:57.737
Regarding the mayoral election

00:05:57.738 --> 00:06:01.116
on the 20th next month,

00:06:01.117 --> 00:06:02.159
the election committee...

00:06:05.246 --> 00:06:06.122
"Comet to pass by in a month:
Visible to the naked eye"

00:06:06.205 --> 00:06:08.583
A comet with an orbital period of

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:11.252
1,200 years will pass by in a month.

00:06:11.586 --> 00:06:13.503
The comet will be visible

00:06:13.504 --> 00:06:15.880
to the naked eye for several days...

00:06:15.881 --> 00:06:17.924
It's time for you to make up with him.

00:06:17.925 --> 00:06:18.968
It's an adult matter.

00:06:19.051 --> 00:06:19.885
"Position of Cornet Tiamat"

00:06:20.052 --> 00:06:21.469
JAXA are preparing to observe

00:06:21.470 --> 00:06:22.680
the celestial show of the century.

00:06:22.763 --> 00:06:23.556
"Closest on October 4th"

00:06:40.197 --> 00:06:41.741
We're going!

00:07:02.178 --> 00:07:04.430
Study hard!

00:07:09.518 --> 00:07:10.977
Mitsuha!

00:07:10.978 --> 00:07:13.021
Morning, Sayaka, Tessie.

00:07:13.022 --> 00:07:13.981
Morning.

00:07:13.982 --> 00:07:16.858
- Get off.
- Why? Meanie.

00:07:16.859 --> 00:07:18.735
- You're heavy.
- That's rude.

00:07:18.736 --> 00:07:20.987
You two get along so well.

00:07:20.988 --> 00:07:22.239
We do not!

00:07:24.867 --> 00:07:27.369
Your hair looks all right today.

00:07:27.370 --> 00:07:28.536
What?

00:07:28.537 --> 00:07:29.455
Yeah,

00:07:29.456 --> 00:07:32.208
- did your grandma exorcise you?
- Exorcise?

00:07:32.375 --> 00:07:34.501
You were totally possessed yesterday!

00:07:34.502 --> 00:07:37.045
Cut out the occultism.

00:07:37.046 --> 00:07:39.881
Mitsuha is just stressed. Right?

00:07:39.882 --> 00:07:42.550
Huh? What are you talking about?

00:07:42.551 --> 00:07:43.886
You don't remember?

00:07:45.346 --> 00:07:47.138
And above all,

00:07:47.139 --> 00:07:49.600
restoring the town's fiscal health

00:07:49.892 --> 00:07:52.977
to continue its revitalization project!

00:07:52.978 --> 00:07:54.896
Only when these are achieved

00:07:54.897 --> 00:07:58.442
can a safe and secure community be created!

00:07:58.818 --> 00:08:00.403
As the incumbent mayor...

00:08:01.112 --> 00:08:03.905
He'll be reelected again anyway.

00:08:03.906 --> 00:08:06.950
I heard he's been dishing out the pork.

00:08:06.951 --> 00:08:08.493
Hey, Miyamizu.

00:08:08.494 --> 00:08:09.870
Morning.

00:08:10.454 --> 00:08:11.996
The mayor's kid and

00:08:11.997 --> 00:08:13.790
his contractor's kid get along too.

00:08:13.791 --> 00:08:14.875
Ew.

00:08:19.463 --> 00:08:20.881
Mitsuha!

00:08:21.549 --> 00:08:23.426
Stand up straight!

00:08:24.552 --> 00:08:26.219
He's strict with his family.

00:08:26.220 --> 00:08:27.762
I'm impressed.

00:08:27.763 --> 00:08:28.888
So embarrassing.

00:08:28.889 --> 00:08:30.141
Pathetic!

00:08:30.850 --> 00:08:32.101
Mitsuha.

00:08:33.394 --> 00:08:35.646
In front of everybody...

00:08:38.858 --> 00:08:40.025
"Who are you?"

00:08:47.450 --> 00:08:49.075
"Tasokare" (Twilight)

00:08:49.076 --> 00:08:52.954
"Tasokare" means "Who is that" and is

00:08:52.955 --> 00:08:55.498
the origin of the word "tasogare-doki."

00:08:55.499 --> 00:08:59.210
Twilight, when it's neither day nor night.

00:08:59.211 --> 00:09:01.254
When the world blurs and one might

00:09:01.255 --> 00:09:04.675
encounter something not human.

00:09:05.176 --> 00:09:08.679
Older expressions include "karetaso-doki"

00:09:09.764 --> 00:09:12.183
and "kawatare-doki."

00:09:12.683 --> 00:09:15.143
I have a question! Not "kataware-doki"?

00:09:15.144 --> 00:09:18.898
"Kataware-doki"? I think
that's a local dialect.

00:09:19.190 --> 00:09:20.482
I've heard that Itomori's elderly

00:09:20.483 --> 00:09:21.525
still use classical language.

00:09:21.609 --> 00:09:22.777
"Who are you?"

00:09:22.902 --> 00:09:24.528
We're in the boonies, after all.

00:09:27.281 --> 00:09:29.449
OK next, Mitsuha.

00:09:29.450 --> 00:09:30.701
Yes.

00:09:31.702 --> 00:09:34.663
Oh, so you remember your name today.

00:09:37.416 --> 00:09:38.918
You don't remember?

00:09:40.878 --> 00:09:42.962
Yesterday you forgot

00:09:42.963 --> 00:09:45.007
where your desk and locker were.

00:09:45.257 --> 00:09:48.302
Your hair is messy with no ribbon.

00:09:50.846 --> 00:09:53.306
What? No way! Really?

00:09:53.307 --> 00:09:55.809
It was like you had amnesia.

00:09:55.810 --> 00:09:57.018
Well,

00:09:57.019 --> 00:10:00.397
I do feel like I've been
in a strange dream lately...

00:10:00.606 --> 00:10:03.317
A dream about someone else's life?

00:10:03.859 --> 00:10:06.612
I can't remember clearly.

00:10:06.987 --> 00:10:09.156
I know! That was...

00:10:09.490 --> 00:10:10.740
your previous life!

00:10:10.741 --> 00:10:11.575
Or maybe

00:10:11.576 --> 00:10:14.787
your subconscious
linked to the Everett multiverse...

00:10:15.037 --> 00:10:16.162
Stay out of this.

00:10:16.163 --> 00:10:19.667
Oh! Tessie, did you write
that in my notebook?

00:10:21.502 --> 00:10:22.753
Nothing.

00:10:23.963 --> 00:10:27.757
But Mitsuha,
you really were a bit weird yesterday.

00:10:27.758 --> 00:10:29.677
Are you feeling alright?

00:10:30.886 --> 00:10:34.222
That's so strange. I feel fine.

00:10:34.223 --> 00:10:35.723
Maybe you are stressful.

00:10:35.724 --> 00:10:38.226
That ritual is coming up, isn't it?

00:10:38.227 --> 00:10:40.728
Oh, don't remind me!

00:10:40.729 --> 00:10:43.274
I can't stand this town anymore.

00:10:43.858 --> 00:10:46.192
It's too small and packed.

00:10:46.193 --> 00:10:49.529
I want to graduate and go to Tokyo.

00:10:49.530 --> 00:10:54.493
I don't blame you.
There's really nothing in here.

00:10:55.995 --> 00:10:58.246
Trains come every 2 hours.

00:10:58.247 --> 00:11:00.290
The store closes at 9 p.m.

00:11:00.291 --> 00:11:02.250
No bookstore. No dentist.

00:11:02.251 --> 00:11:03.002
"Pub Mother" "Pub Cat's Eye"

00:11:03.085 --> 00:11:04.837
But have 2 pubs for some reason.

00:11:05.004 --> 00:11:05.880
No jobs.

00:11:05.881 --> 00:11:07.088
No brides.

00:11:07.089 --> 00:11:09.425
Short sunlight hours.

00:11:11.176 --> 00:11:13.470
- Give me a break!
- What?

00:11:14.680 --> 00:11:17.223
I mean... How about we stop by a cafe?

00:11:17.224 --> 00:11:18.892
- A cafe?
- Really?

00:11:18.893 --> 00:11:20.144
Where?

00:11:24.273 --> 00:11:27.192
Hello.

00:11:31.906 --> 00:11:33.531
This is a cafe?

00:11:33.532 --> 00:11:35.367
You knew there wasn't one.

00:11:35.743 --> 00:11:38.203
Mitsuha just went home.

00:11:39.330 --> 00:11:41.789
Things must be rough for her.

00:11:41.790 --> 00:11:44.292
Because she is the center stage.

00:11:44.293 --> 00:11:45.586
Yeah.

00:11:48.505 --> 00:11:50.131
Hey, Tessie.

00:11:50.132 --> 00:11:51.091
What?

00:11:51.842 --> 00:11:54.261
What will you do after you graduate?

00:11:54.762 --> 00:11:56.304
What's this?

00:11:56.305 --> 00:11:57.681
Are you asking about my future?

00:11:59.308 --> 00:12:00.642
Nothing special.

00:12:00.643 --> 00:12:04.396
I'll probably keep on
living a normal life in this town.

00:12:20.496 --> 00:12:22.623
I'd rather do that too.

00:12:22.873 --> 00:12:25.583
You're not ready yet, Yotsuha.

00:12:25.584 --> 00:12:27.711
Listen to the thread's voice.

00:12:28.003 --> 00:12:31.214
When you keep twining like that,

00:12:31.215 --> 00:12:33.216
emotions will eventually start flowing

00:12:33.217 --> 00:12:35.010
between you and the thread.

00:12:35.594 --> 00:12:37.220
Threads don't talk.

00:12:37.221 --> 00:12:39.347
She means, "Focus."

00:12:39.348 --> 00:12:41.642
1,000 years of Itomori's history is etched

00:12:42.059 --> 00:12:45.311
into our braided cords.

00:12:45.312 --> 00:12:49.273
Listen. 200 years ago...

00:12:49.274 --> 00:12:50.858
Here she goes again.

00:12:50.859 --> 00:12:54.070
Sandal maker Mayugoro's bathroom caught

00:12:54.071 --> 00:12:57.991
on fire and burned down
the whole area around.

00:12:57.992 --> 00:13:01.036
The shrine and old documents were destroyed

00:13:01.453 --> 00:13:02.912
and this is known as...

00:13:02.913 --> 00:13:04.665
The Great Fire of Mayugoro.

00:13:04.999 --> 00:13:09.294
The fire has his name? Poor Mayugoro.

00:13:09.712 --> 00:13:13.256
So the meaning of our festivals became

00:13:13.257 --> 00:13:15.759
unknown and only the formality lived on.

00:13:16.593 --> 00:13:18.594
But even if words are lost,

00:13:18.595 --> 00:13:20.430
tradition should be handed down.

00:13:20.431 --> 00:13:25.019
That's our responsbility
at Miyamizu Shrine.

00:13:27.688 --> 00:13:31.650
But that foolish son-in-law...

00:13:32.735 --> 00:13:36.822
He not only left Shinto
priesthood but also.

00:13:37.156 --> 00:13:40.033
Play politics? He's hopeless.

00:13:40.034 --> 00:13:42.453
Have one more, my man.

00:13:45.414 --> 00:13:47.707
I'm counting on your help again.

00:13:47.708 --> 00:13:49.417
Leave it to me.

00:13:49.418 --> 00:13:53.046
You'll get votes from the Kadoiri
and Sakagami Districts.

00:13:53.047 --> 00:13:54.505
How's it going with her?

00:13:54.506 --> 00:13:56.258
It's not that easy.

00:13:58.135 --> 00:14:00.262
I smell corruption.

00:14:00.345 --> 00:14:01.847
Don't be ridiculous.

00:14:02.473 --> 00:14:04.849
Bring us a few more hot sake.

00:14:04.850 --> 00:14:06.100
OK.

00:14:06.101 --> 00:14:08.770
Katsuhiko, come help on site this weekend.

00:14:08.771 --> 00:14:10.897
Learn how to use explosives.

00:14:10.898 --> 00:14:12.148
Yes.

00:14:12.149 --> 00:14:13.316
Can't hear you.

00:14:13.317 --> 00:14:14.276
Yes!

00:14:27.664 --> 00:14:30.667
We both have had enough, don't we?

00:14:48.852 --> 00:14:51.854
Is that Yotsuha? She's all grown up.

00:14:51.855 --> 00:14:54.525
They're both pretty like their mother.

00:14:56.318 --> 00:14:57.402
Hey.

00:14:57.653 --> 00:14:59.029
Hey.

00:15:30.936 --> 00:15:33.480
It's the oldest sake in the world.

00:15:34.064 --> 00:15:36.691
By chewing on rice, spitting it out,

00:15:36.692 --> 00:15:39.485
and letting it ferment, it becomes alcohol.

00:15:39.486 --> 00:15:41.071
"Kuchikamisake."

00:15:41.530 --> 00:15:44.574
Do the gods appreciate sake made that way?

00:15:44.575 --> 00:15:46.243
Of course they do.

00:15:48.328 --> 00:15:50.747
Hey, look. It's Miyamizu.

00:15:56.378 --> 00:15:58.713
Oh! I could never do that!

00:15:58.714 --> 00:16:00.381
Isn't she embarrassed?

00:16:00.382 --> 00:16:02.092
I can't believe it.

00:16:16.356 --> 00:16:18.775
Cheer up, Mitsuha.

00:16:19.109 --> 00:16:21.611
Who cares if a few classmates saw you?

00:16:21.612 --> 00:16:24.531
I envy your "pre-pubescent"
carefree attitude.

00:16:24.907 --> 00:16:28.159
Why not sell lots of kuchikamisake and

00:16:28.160 --> 00:16:29.785
use the money to go to Tokyo?

00:16:29.786 --> 00:16:32.330
Where do you get such ideas?

00:16:32.331 --> 00:16:35.166
Sell them with photos and making videos.

00:16:35.167 --> 00:16:38.085
Name it "Shrine Maiden's Sake."

00:16:38.086 --> 00:16:39.671
You'll make money!

00:16:40.672 --> 00:16:42.382
"Shrine Maiden's Sake"

00:16:43.050 --> 00:16:45.636
No. That breaks the Liquor Tax Law.

00:16:47.262 --> 00:16:49.139
That's the problem?

00:16:54.978 --> 00:16:59.941
I hate this town! I hate this life!

00:16:59.942 --> 00:17:04.488
Please make me a handsome Tokyo boy
in my next life!

00:17:08.492 --> 00:17:10.369
What a fool...

00:17:38.313 --> 00:17:39.273
Ow!

00:17:42.067 --> 00:17:44.111
Ouch...

00:17:52.703 --> 00:17:53.870
Where...

00:18:05.257 --> 00:18:08.051
Something's there...

00:18:21.440 --> 00:18:22.565
Ow!

00:18:22.566 --> 00:18:24.359
Taki, Are you up?

00:18:26.611 --> 00:18:28.821
It was your turn to cook.

00:18:28.822 --> 00:18:29.989
Wake up on time.

00:18:29.990 --> 00:18:31.533
I'm sorry.

00:18:32.784 --> 00:18:36.079
I'm going now. Drink all the miso soup.

00:18:36.455 --> 00:18:37.289
OK.

00:18:37.789 --> 00:18:40.082
Go to school even if you're late.

00:18:40.083 --> 00:18:41.209
See you.

00:18:42.336 --> 00:18:43.670
Have a nice day.

00:18:55.015 --> 00:18:56.475
What a strange dream.

00:18:58.101 --> 00:19:00.479
"From Tsukasa: Run, you're late!"

00:19:01.938 --> 00:19:06.443
What? Who's it from? Tsukasa? Who's that?

00:19:16.119 --> 00:19:17.913
I have to use the bathroom.

00:19:26.797 --> 00:19:28.507
This is too realistic.

00:20:18.932 --> 00:20:19.975
"Shinjuku Station"

00:20:39.619 --> 00:20:41.746
I'm in Tokyo.

00:20:46.209 --> 00:20:47.377
"Jingu High School"

00:20:48.712 --> 00:20:50.671
- Where'd you get it?
- Daikanyama.

00:20:50.672 --> 00:20:52.590
The front act at the next gig...

00:20:52.591 --> 00:20:55.510
Let's skip club and go to a movie.

00:21:00.348 --> 00:21:01.808
Taki!

00:21:03.143 --> 00:21:06.980
Arriving at noon, huh? Let's eat lunch.

00:21:07.397 --> 00:21:08.939
You ignored my message

00:21:08.940 --> 00:21:10.816
Oh, Tsukasa?

00:21:10.817 --> 00:21:13.612
At least you sound apologetic.

00:21:15.447 --> 00:21:16.864
You got lost?

00:21:16.865 --> 00:21:17.865
Yeah.

00:21:17.866 --> 00:21:21.535
How could you get lost
on the way to school?

00:21:21.536 --> 00:21:25.206
- Uh... Well... I (watashi)...
- Feminine?

00:21:25.207 --> 00:21:26.708
I (watakushi)!

00:21:27.250 --> 00:21:28.376
I (boku)?

00:21:29.002 --> 00:21:30.045
I (ore)?

00:21:32.214 --> 00:21:34.340
I was enjoying myself.

00:21:34.341 --> 00:21:38.011
It's so festive to me all in Tokyo.

00:21:38.386 --> 00:21:40.388
You seem to have a dialect.

00:21:40.889 --> 00:21:42.098
Where's your lunch?

00:21:42.807 --> 00:21:45.518
- Geez.
- Are you half asleep?

00:21:45.519 --> 00:21:46.644
You got something?

00:21:46.645 --> 00:21:48.688
Croquette-egg sandwich sounds good!

00:21:52.943 --> 00:21:54.110
Thank you.

00:21:56.363 --> 00:21:57.863
Let's go to a cafe.

00:21:57.864 --> 00:22:00.200
Oh that one? OK. Corning, Taki?

00:22:00.575 --> 00:22:03.619
What? What? What?

00:22:03.620 --> 00:22:04.621
A cafe?

00:22:08.333 --> 00:22:10.000
Nice timberwork up there.

00:22:10.001 --> 00:22:11.962
Yeah, they attented to details.

